<p>Well they finaly done it... *cries* I just said the other day &quot;watch everyone is playing a bard and has learned how to AE kite, they will nerf it&quot;....... here are my thoughts, Yes in someone ways this ability was Way to powerful... (Altough I hate they got rid of it and will miss it dearly) What they could have done is made our AE spells hit only 4 like Druids, so we could Quad kinda... I don't know maybe that woulnd't work.. Any way, now what, can a bard still solo... Well yes, and no... Just its a little (lot) slower. We can still Charm, and Fear kite, and if your really talented both at the same time. You can still Dot kite, with our Chant songs, but this will mean single pulls *cries again*, however we are not down and out. Just leveling slower :-(. I dont balme them though.. I would make a human bard and then make a second character on another account and play them with the bard, have the bard solo kite from 8 to 45 (gets a little slower here until a little later) and would PL in a way 2 classes. I could do 10 levels a day easy for both classes, At least until 45 then like I said it would slow down. I will miss the mindless hours of running around in circles. Watching as others stair in horror as 20 Red mobs chase a level 9 only to watch him (15 mins later) kill them all with out a scratch. Then repeat the process. *ponders* wonder how many 65th level bards will quit now that they cant solo in the planes.. I was so looking forward to that. Oh well. Maybe they will suprise us and give us a new trick that will help us. Just my thoughts. (PS sorry for mispellings...)</p>
