<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />as a 65 druid, I can pull an AA every 15 min in PoF tables with a group, that is safe, steady not much risk XP, then you take a bard, 20 minutes per success to get 1.75 AA in PoV or more in HoH, but if you add in the times you die after 15 minutes and getting mobs down to 10% then poof... LOADING. it all evens out.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />What are you talking about? 20 minutes to get 1.75 AA in PoV? MAYBE if you kite the ENTIRE zone, in which case you are creating zone disruption and lagging out the servers. And more in HoH? You realize if you pull more then 10 they start gating back, right? And an AA every 15 minutes in PoF tables in a group... not likely. Maybe if it's a REALLY awesome Time enable group, but not likely otherwise.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />A bard is almost exclusivly a solo class, if you don't belive me, try one. <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />I have heard some say (AKA the ones who never could hack the skill) that the comprimise of the other effects still hitting moving targets was livable, but who REALLY wanted this? <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />Ok, my bard is level 64 at the moment. I DID AE kite a bit in the 30's and 40's, but I've swarmed some since and primarily grouped. Also, you apparently don't understand the nerf. Originally, they were making it so that if the BARD was moving, any AE DoT he had running would be reduced to MELEE RANGE ONLY. They were going to go live with this nerf, wether we liked it or not. This meant our AE slows and resist debuffs would also be effected.They offered us the chance to help them come up with an alternative. The nerf as it stands: If the MOB wants to move during the server tick, the DAMAGE portion will not take effect, but the OTHER parts will. This allows us to still use our songs for other purposes. <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />same with a bard, you spend huge amounts of time learning a skill, tons of time on CR's, and even then you have a high failure rate<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />It's not nearly as hard as you make it out to be. Granted, I haven't AE'd the PoF tables myself, but once you have the skill, the only thing that chnages is how tight your circles have to be. I died 5 times before I got my first successful kite. Then I made all that experience I lost back in 2 successful kites that took me 20 minutes each. I died one more time in the next 10 levels! And that was solely due to a lag spike. When the primary reasons bards die from AEing is lag spikes, you can't claim some superior skill. If you've been following this topic on the other bard forums at all, you'd know that the server lag caused by bards trailing 20-100 mobs behind them, all doing collision and movement calculations was causing servers to lag out. When a server lags out that badly, it doesn't only effect THAT bard, it effects EVERYONE on that server.  <br /> <br />Oh, and BTW, many of the bards that are crying the hardest about this nerf (AKA mostly the ones that can't hack it in a group) are blaming the druids, and are trying to scratch up reasons to call for druid nerfs next. [:wink:]  <br /> <br /></p>
